properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 18 at 3:23AM CST until January 19 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Omaha/Valley NE
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Winter Weather Advisory, Areas of blowing snow.
Visibility down to 1/2 mile at times. Winds gusting as high as
55 mph. For the Wind Chill Advisory, very cold wind chills
expected. Wind chills as low as 25 below zero.

* WHERE...Portions of east central and northeast Nebraska and
southwest and west central Iowa.

* WHEN...For the Winter Weather Advisory, until 6 AM CST early
this morning. For the Wind Chill Advisory, from 4 AM to noon
CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Areas of blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. Strong winds could
cause extensive damage to trees and power lines. The cold wind
chills could cause frostbite on exposed skin in as little as
30 minutes tonight.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
